        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>curves (rulers) [300022493], rulers (measuring devices) [300266529], linear distance measuring devices [300198750], distance measuring devices [300195705], measuring devices for extent [300195701], measuring devices (instruments) [300207870], Measuring Devices (hierarchy name) [300207851], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Thin, rigid pieces of clear plastic or some other material, cut in a continuously curved or scroll shape; used as a guide for ruling curves through a series of points that are not on the arc of a circle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026701/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dunne, onbuigzame stukken doorzichtig plastic of ander materiaal die in een doorlopende gebogen of gekrulde vorm zijn gesneden. Worden gebruikt als geleiders om bogen te tekenen door middel van een reeks punten die niet binnen de boog van een cirkel vallen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dünnes, starres und durchsichtiges Stück aus Plastik oder anderem Material in der Form einer stetigen Kurve oder Schnecke; wird zum Zeichnen von Kurven entlang einer Reihe von Punkten verwendet, die nicht auf einem Kreisbogen liegen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pièces minces et rigides en plastique transparent ou dans un autre matériau, découpées en forme de courbe continue ou de volute. Il s’agit d’un guide pour tracer des courbes à travers une série de points qui ne sont pas sur l’arc de cercle.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>French</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000305/BEINFRAT </Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000115330/BEINFRAT-network (2022)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
